cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the application of machine learning models for the computational staining and destaining of histopathology tissue samples. The use of generative adversarial neural networks for this purpose falls under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the training of these models. Additionally, the paper deals with the analysis and comparison of structural and anatomical details of the generated images, which falls under the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
